            {
              "id": "hs-defi-s2-il-note",
              "type": "text",
              "left": 24,
              "top": 342,
              "width": 460,
              "height": 60,
              "rotate": 0,
              "content": "<p style='font-size:12px;color:#94a3b8;line-height:1.7;'>IL is 'impermanent' because if prices return to entry levels, it disappears. It only becomes a realized loss when you withdraw while prices have moved. Swap fee income can offset it.</p>",
